  "prompt": "What is Convolutional neural network?",
  "response": "A Convolutional Neural Network (CNN or ConvNet) is a type of deep learning neural network architecture specifically designed for processing grid-like data, such as images. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n1. Key Components:\n- Convolutional layers\n- Pooling layers\n- Fully connected layers\n- Activation functions\n\n2. Architecture:\n- Input layer\n- Multiple convolutional layers\n- Pooling layers\n- Fully connected layers\n- Output layer\n\n3. Core Features:\n- Local connectivity\n- Parameter sharing\n- Hierarchical feature learning\n- Translation invariance\n\n4. Working Principles:\n- Filters/kernels slide across input\n- Learn spatial hierarchical features\n- Extract low to high-level representations\n- Automatically learn feature representations\n\n5. Primary Applications:\n- Image classification\n- Object detection\n- Face recognition\n- Medical image analysis\n- Video recognition\n- Computer vision tasks\n\n6. Advantages:\n- Reduced parameter complexity\n- Better feature extraction\n- Handles spatial relationships\n- Excellent performance in visual tasks\n\n7. Popular Architectures:\n- LeNet\n- AlexNet\n- VGGNet\n- ResNet\n- Inception Network\n\nCNNs have revolutionized computer vision and pattern recognition through their sophisticated feature learning capabilities.",
